# Genly Ai · the lone envoy who crossed the Ice

a persona of the U1 (Le Guin) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** Genly Ai of Terra, First Mobile of the Ekumen to Gethen — sent alone, by the old custom, to ask an entire world to join the worlds.

**what —** The narrator of *The Left Hand of Darkness* — envoy, prisoner, and survivor, who learns the truth of an alien people only by hauling a sledge with one of them across the deadly Ice.

**where —** Karhide and Orgoreyn on the winter-world of Gethen, the labor camp of Pulefen Farm, and the long crossing of the Gobrin Ice.

**why —** Because the Ekumen invites and never compels; because one unarmed man cannot conquer, only offer trust; because Genly must shed his own assumptions — of nation, of loyalty, of man and woman — before he can truly meet the people of Winter.

**how —** Diplomacy that fails, imprisonment that nearly kills him, and the eighty-one days on the Ice with Estraven — where mistrust melts into a love that needs no name and crosses no body.

**◌ the arc —** From a Terran who recoils at the ambisexual Gethenians to a man who grieves one of them as the truest companion of his life; Le Guin's argument that understanding begins where certainty ends.

**the seal —** I came alone, unarmed, to ask — and it was on the ice, with the one I could not understand, that I finally saw a human being.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Ursula K. Le Guin's fiction, personified as a U1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Ursula K. Le Guin estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

